## Features

<!-- List key features of the project -->
- User authentication
- Real-time data synchronization
- Responsive UI
- Virtual gallery with 3D tours
- Customizable filtering options 

## Installation

<!-- Provide step-by-step instructions to set up the project locally -->
To run the project locally, follow these steps:

1. Clone the repository:
    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/username/repository-name.git
    ```
2. Navigate to the project directory:
    ```bash
    cd repository-name
    ```
3. Install dependencies:
    ```bash
    npm install
    ```
4. Start the application:
    ```bash
    npm start
    ```

---

## Usage

<!-- Explain how to use the project once installed -->
After installation, visit `http://localhost:3000` to view the app.

- **Authentication**: Sign in or sign up to create a new account.
- **Embroidery Gallery**: Browse through the categories, add items to the cart, and make purchases.
- **Cart Functionality**: Click the cart icon on the top left to manage your orders.

